{
  "text": "where kAk 2 and kAk F are the spectral norm and the Frobenius norm of A, respectively. Their main result [CITATION_1] Theorem 2] states that any iterative sequence {x k } \u221e k=0 , generated by Algorithm 1, converges to the solution of the system Ax = b with an expected exponential rate, and that the rate of convergence depends on the scaled condition number \u03ba(A).",
